						<summary>

						<p>This is a damaged record probably of the same king (<hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi>), mentioning a gift of 91 sheep for a lamp. The temple authorities who received the gift agreed to make an offering of rice in addition, to the deity on the day of Pushya in the month of Tai.</p>						

